[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    2000[0m:[38;5;10m[49m The ingestion pipeline does nine things in order. First, it routes to the right per-source adapter. Second, it parses and validates the raw message. Third, it classifies sensitive-record category for downstream consent enforcement. Fourth, it verifies the patient's current consent posture (not a cached snapshot, because consent is revocable). Fifth, it writes a provenance-journal entry on a separately-managed KMS path. Sixth, it normalizes the event into the coordination-state schema. Seventh, it reconciles against existing state. Eighth, it updates the coordination state with provenance references preserved. Ninth, it emits care-event triggers for the seam-detection rule engine and the protocol-trigger evaluator. Skip any of these and the assistant has no defensible relationship with the cross-organizational data it depends on.
