[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    2270[0m:[38;5;10m[49m The seam-detection step does six things in order. First, it loads the patient's coordination state. Second, it runs each applicable rule against the state and the incoming event, with each rule contributing its detection, confidence, and evidence. Third, it persists detected seams to the seam-flag store and emits seam-flag-raised events. Fourth, it evaluates protocol triggers (e.g., a discharge event initiates the appropriate transition workflow). Fifth, it routes care-team-resolvable items to the alert queue. Sixth, it escalates high-acuity findings immediately to the human queue. The rules are institutional content; the engine is the deterministic floor on which the LLM operates.
