[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    2530[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ```
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    2531[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    2532[0m:[38;5;10m[49m The conversation receive step does five things in order. First, it identifies or creates the conversation-state record. Second, it runs input safety including continuous emergency screening and sensitive-disclosure detection; emergencies route immediately to the right pathway, sensitive disclosures route without ending the conversation. Third, it confirms the speaker role (patient or caregiver) from the verified session. Fourth, it loads the role-specific record (patient-coordination record or caregiver record with proxy-access scope). Fifth, it loads the coordination state scoped by the speaker's role. The output is either an early-exit response or the intermediate payload that Step 5 turns into a generated response.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    2533[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    2534[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ---
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    2535[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    2536[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ## Step 5: Run the Agent's Tool-Use Loop with Citation Discipline
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    2537[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    2538[0m:[38;5;10m[49m The agent takes the user's utterance, decides what coordination tools to call, retrieves the necessary state and protocols, and composes a grounded response. Each tool call is recorded in the tool-call ledger; each retrieved citation is preserved in the response trace. The LLM does not fabricate coordination-state assertions; if a tool returns "unknown," the assistant says so honestly.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    2539[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    2540[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ```python
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    2541[0m:[38;5;10m[49m def handle_conversation(*,
