[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    3261[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         "protocol_id":
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    3262[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             transition_protocol["protocol_id"],
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    3263[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         "execution_id":      execution["execution_id"],
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    3264[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     }
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    3265[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ```
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    3266[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    3267[0m:[38;5;10m[49m The transition orchestration step does six things in order. First, it selects the appropriate protocol based on discharge destination and admission type. Second, it starts the Step Functions execution that drives the workflow. Third, it persists the transition record with the protocol-defined steps and their initial status. Fourth, it schedules the welcome-home check-in. Fifth, it delivers the red-flag warnings up front. Sixth, it emits the transition-initiated event. The state machine drives the protocol; the LLM operates on top of it as the conversational interface.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    3268[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    3269[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ---
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    3270[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    3271[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ## Step 8: Track Referral Lifecycles to Closure
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    3272[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    3273[0m:[38;5;10m[49m Referrals are first-class coordination objects with a structured lifecycle. The referral-lifecycle subsystem is a deterministic state machine; the LLM operates on top of it.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    3274[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    3275[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ```python
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    3276[0m:[38;5;10m[49m def handle_referral_event(*, patient_id, referral_event):
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    3277[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     """
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    3278[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     Process a referral lifecycle event. Validates the state
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    3279[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     transition, persists the new state, emits the lifecycle
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    3280[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     event, and schedules the next protocol-driven action.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    3281[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     """
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    3282[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     referral_id = referral_event["referral_id"]
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    3283[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     event_type = referral_event["event_type"]
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    3284[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         # values: "ordered", "communicated_to_patient",
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    3285[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         # "scheduled", "rescheduled", "attended",
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    3286[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         # "no_showed", "cancelled",
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    3287[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         # "consult_note_received", "closed"
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    3288[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    3289[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     # Step 8A: load current referral state.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    3290[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     ref_table = dynamodb.Table(REFERRAL_LIFECYCLE_TABLE)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    3291[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     response = ref_table.get_item(
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    3292[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         Key={"referral_id": referral_id})
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    3293[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     current = response.get("Item")
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    3294[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    3295[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     # Step 8B: validate the state transition. Reject events
